snippet.textDisplay:
Watched the full game; massive respect and credit to Nuno and his players. Extremely disciplined, and well drilled. Everyone works hard for each other, and they stretched us for large parts of the second half.
Anyone saying Mo is selfish, or should be sold etc, pull your head in. He is an integral part of the team. If you are only looking at the couple of chances he had to pass tonight, rather than shoot, then you completely miss all the pressing and off the ball running he does. Why do you think he was absolutely knackered at the end, and needed to be subbed?
We won't always be clinical, high energy, and the completely dominant team. It's a lot easier to get up for a game against a league leader, than it is to do what we are currently doing. That's why it's so special. Cause it's not something done every year.
Not since the lads in the 80s, have I thought we can honestly win every game we play. Even if we don't, it's been a special season. Need to still win it, before I'll say we've won it. Been around football, and a Liverpool supporter, too long to jump that gun.
